We have trouble feeding , providing fresh , clean water , medicines , fuel for the six and a half billion .
It is going to be a stretch to do it for nine .
We use over five billion tons of coal , 30 billion-plus barrels of oil -- that is a hundred million barrels a day .
When we try to think of biological processes or any process to replace that , it is going to be a huge challenge .
Then of course , there is all that CO2 from this material that ends up in the atmosphere .
We now , from our discovery around the world , have a database with about 20 million genes , and I like to think of these as the design components of the future .
