And innovation really stopped in this industry quite some ago , so the idea that there is some good ideas laying around is not all that surprising .
The idea of Terrapower is that , instead of burning a part of uranium , the one percent , which is the U235 , we decided , let is burn the 99 percent , the U238 .
It is kind of a crazy idea .
In fact , people had talked about it for a long time , but they could never simulate properly whether it would work or not , and so it is through the advent of modern supercomputers that now you can simulate and see that , yes , with the right material 's approach , this looks like it would work .
And , because you are burning that 99 percent , you have greatly improved cost profile .
You actually burn up the waste , and you can actually use as fuel all the leftover waste from today 's reactors .
So , instead of worrying about them , you just take that . It is a great thing .
It breathes this uranium as it goes along . So it is kind of like a candle .
You can see it is a log there , often referred to as a traveling wave reactor .
In terms of fuel , this really solves the problem .
I have got a picture here of a place in Kentucky .
This is the left over , the 99 percent , where they have taken out the part they burn now , so it is called depleted uranium .
That would power the U.S. for hundreds of years .
And , simply by filtering sea water in an inexpensive process , you would have enough fuel for the entire lifetime of the rest of the planet .
